A Simple Guide to MPD Server with MPDroid

Nomi Shaw Linux, MPD February 14, 2019February 14, 2019 2 Minutes

MPDroid is an Android application that lets you control MPD remotely with your Android phone and also can stream music to your Android phone remotely over MPD Server. Heres what you will need:

A machine that can run MPD server, It can be your Laptop or a Raspberry Pi. Just install mpd on your machine and make the following changes to your mpd configuration

If you dont know how to set up MPD on your Linux machine, then read my previos blog on MPD. Setting up MPD in Linux (Mint/Ubuntu)

audio_output {
type        "httpd"
name        "My HTTP Stream"
encoder     "vorbis"        # optional, vorbis or lame
port        "8000"
#bind_to_address "127.0.0.1"               # optional, IPv4 or IPv6
quality     "5.0"           # do not define if bitrate is defined
bitrate     "128"           # do not define if quality is defined
format      "44100:16:1"
max_clients     "0"                     # optional 0=no limit
}

Search for bind_to_address in your mpd.conf and comment it in, or simply delete it. Also look for port 6600 and comment it out by deleting # at the start of the line.

Our configuration just completed now we need to open some ports in order to access it remotely. We need to expose 6600 port which is used by mpd by default and 8000 port which is used by audio_output

$ sudo ufw allow 6600/tcp

$ sudo ufw allow 8000/tcp

Now check if your firewall is active or not, because if your doing it for the first time the chances are that your firewall is inactive. You can check it by:

$ sudo ufw status

It will return Status saying active or inactive. If its inactive just enable it by

$ sudo ufw enable

Now install MPDroid on your Android from Playstore and make the following changes

In the first option Host enter the IP Address of your host on which you have setup your mpd server. In Linux you can get it by ifconfig command. In the second option enter the port 6600 which is by default. For the third option, check your mpd.conf file and search for the line password, by default the password is password. In the streaming host option again enter your host IP as you entered in the first option. Now go back and wait for MPDroid to make the connection and youre all done.
